[normal]Procedural [bold]as opposed to substantive defects in decision-making[bold]“There is no doubt that one of the virtues of pro
[normal]cedurally fair decision-making is that it is liable to result in better decisions, by ensuring that the decision-maker receives all relevant information and that it is properly tested…. the purpose of a fair hearing is not merely to improve the chances of 
[normal]the tribunal reaching the right decision. At least two other important values are also engaged.”
